# SAP S/4 Hana Fiori Security


SAP - Systems, Applications and Products in Data Processing

- Leading ERP Enterprose Resource planning software.
- Modules: Finance, HR, Logistics, & Manufacturers.
- SAP ERP, SAP S/4 HANA, SAP on Premise, SAP on Cloud.

##### What is SAP S/4 Hana?
- SAP S/4 Hana is a next gen ERP suite, optimized for the in-memory SAP HANA database. 
- It delivers simplified data models.
- Real time analytics
- Enhanced user experiences through fiori apps.

##### What is SAP HANA?
- SAP HANA is an in-memory database and development platform designed from scratch to be used for thier ER suite.
- This enables fast processing and real time analytics

##### What is Fiori?
- SAP Fiori is a design system and UX approach that provides users with modern, intutive, and role based experience across devices. it replaces the GUI with apps & tiles.

- Modern look replacement for old SAP GUI
- Responsive design - accessible on any device like mobile, Tab, desktop.
- Rapid deployment - web technology at core HTML5/Odata/Javascript.
- SAPUI5 Framework - Design guidlines.
- T-code to Fiori Launchpad: /n/ui2/flp

##### What is RISE with SAP?
- Rise with SAP is a subscription based offering combining S/4 Hana infrastructure, and transformation services into a single contract for cloud transformations.

#### Fiori Deployment:

##### Embedded Deployment:
- Fiori (FES) server runs on same server where the backend runs infrastructure cost reduced.
- If we have one ECC system than this setup is suitable. as it would decrease security complexity.
- performance boost - faster UI load.

- Only draw back is that if backend crashes access will be lost.

##### Hub Deployment:
- Seperate Front end server running Fiori (FES), connected via RFCs. more infrastructure cost.

- This is suited for customer with multiple ECC systems and want to use Fiori as UI. (This is not a future proof for S/4 hana which goes with embedded deployment).
- Security and configuration will be complicated as multiple system level security to be enhanced.


##### SAP BTP / Build Work Zone
- To establish a central point of access to multiple S/4 HANA systems & other SAP products. The recomendation is to use SAP Build work zone on SAP BTP (Cloud Foundry).

- This will be logged into signle sign on into Build work zone and based upon tiles and its target mapping it will automatically redirect the correct S/4 Hana system.




